description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for Trainee Advanced Clinical Practitioners (ACP) to join the Cardiothoracic team at Hull University Teaching Hospitals. The posts will be based at the Cardiac centre at Castle Hill Hospital, Cottingham. We would like to hear from experienced registered healthcare professionals who are critical thinkers and are passionate about transforming care within cardiothoracic surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have professional registration which gives you the ability to prescribe as you will be undertaking Non-medical prescribing as part of the MSc Advanced Clinical Practice at the University of Hull. Practical training and completion of a competency package will take place during the 3 year training period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Upon successful completion of the training programme, as a Qualified ACP, you will progress to AFC Band 8a.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once deemed competent at various points throughout the programme, you will be required to undertake advanced clinical assessment and examination of patients, initiate clinical interventions and treatments, and provide continuity of care from a medical perspective. During training the hours of work will be between Monday to Friday 08.00 to 17.30&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for a challenging yet rewarding position we would welcome your application. We are therefore looking for individuals who have significant post- qualifying experience and have the drive, ambition and positivity to make this role succeed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not apply”&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trust Lead Advanced Practitioner: Karen Jarvis at Karen.jarvis@hey.nhs.uk or 07876 281562&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr David Zicho: Locum Cardiac Surgeon at David.Zicho@hey.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr Vasileios Tentzeris; Thoracic Surgery Consultant at Vasileios.Tentzeris@hey.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
